They refused to leave the country at his command, but tried to gain time by insincere negotiations. He out- witted them, surprised their camp, and defeated them with great loss, and thereafter built a bridge over the Rhine, by which he crossed into Ger- many, where he spent eighteen days, no one daring to offer any resistente to his movements.
